- The volume of the skull in an adult skull is the same for every person
- The equator of the ball is the brow line
- Halfway up from the brow line to the north pole is the hairline
- symmetry line := the line bisecting the north and south pole
- draw a tangent line from the brow line down and you get the line for the nose
- The height of the forehead := browline to hairline. This is the length of the nose


